                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Northeast on Tata Tele radar
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Calcutta, April 10: Tata Teleservices Ltd (TTSL) will invest Rs 500 crore in the next three years in the Northeast, including Assam.        
	The company announced an alliance with the Assam Small Industries Development Corporation (ASIDC) to attract investment and develop telecommunications infrastructure in the state.        
	A release said TTSL would promote local entrepreneurs to set up and manage the sale of telecommunication-related services. It would provide modern communication access to rural and co-operative banks and enable them to make the transition to core banking.        
	TTSL would help the Assam industrial body in connecting state hospitals.        
	The agreement between the two covers the setting up of PCOs, which will provide services such as money transfer, railway and airline reservations.        
	According to Debasish Sur, president, enterprise business unit, TTSL, This partnership with the ASIDC is a great beginning for us to cater to the people of Assam and the rest of the Northeast. Modern telecom facilities such as video-conferencing, voice calling and data transfer will greatly enhance the local and export businesses from the states.                                                                                                                                                       
